<H3> <TI>   DPS Leaders Condemned, Compared to Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703104094 Podgorica MONITOR in Serbo-Croatian 11 Mar 94 p 
5 </F>

<F P=103> AU1703104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Podgorica MONITOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<FÊP=106> [Article by <PERSON>Miodrag Perovic</PERSON>: "Herzeg-Montenegro"] </F>
  [Text] "Take me east of <ORGANIZATION>Suez</ORGANIZATION> where there is no difference 
between the best and the worst," <ORGANIZATION>Rudyard Kipling</ORGANIZATION> wished once. 
This week it was not necessary to travel that far in order to 
reach a world in which fantasy and reality meet. The second <ORGANIZATION>DPS</ORGANIZATION> 
[Democratic Party of Socialists] congress was the place in which 
the desired and the twisted world in which we live, led by the 
<ORGANIZATION>DPS</ORGANIZATION> and its leaders, were equalized. 
  <ORGANIZATION>DPS</ORGANIZATION> members said in the congress that they were devoted to 
democracy, but at the same time they use wiretaps and physical 
threats and misuse the media, which are more brutal than the 
communist television during the last 50 years. They claim to be 
establishing a constitutional state and torture people in 
prisons. They make statements in which they point out that they 
pursue the politics of peace and friendly relations with their 
neighbors, but they have obviously forgotten that they led a war 
outside <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> and sowed 250 graves over the country for 
Montenegrin youngsters who died in that war. They pretend to be 
developing a civilized state, while supporting ethnic cleansing 
not only in <LOCATION>Bosnia</LOCATION>, but also in <LOCATION>Boka Kotorska</LOCATION> and in northern 
<LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION>. They support political pluralism and parliamentary 
democracy but they arm their political followers. They boast 
about the safety <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> citizens allegedly have, but they 
"forget" to mention the act of kidnapping in <LOCATION>Strpci</LOCATION>, in which 
they were involved. They are trying to convince us that their 
foreign policy is constructive and assessed positively by the 
whole world, but their plane can only fly to <LOCATION>Greece</LOCATION> in order to 
buy furniture for their new apartments there. They are open to 
all democratic ideas, but "their attitudes are completely 
identical" with those of the fascist <PERSON>Zhirinovsky</PERSON>. They 
conducted a "secret" poll about public matters and invited the 
manager of an "independent" institute of an "autonomous" 
university to the party congress in order to read what they 
wrote for him. Their bells [the state media] were ringing two 
days long telling us that according to that objective poll more 
than <PERCENT>70 percent</PERCENT> of the 1,000 respondents support <LOCATION>Yugoslavia</LOCATION>, but 
they did not say that less than <PERCENT>5 percent</PERCENT> supported an alliance 
of Serbian states, called <LOCATION>Yugoslavia</LOCATION>, into which they want to 
push <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION>, too. 
  <PERSON>Momir Bulatovic</PERSON> and <PERSON>Milo Djukanovic</PERSON> revived the idea that 
<LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Herzegovina</LOCATION> should merge. They did not state the 
reasons, so we cannot think of their opposite in order to know 
what their real motives are, but let us mention two possible 
reasons in order to make things clearer. One of the reasons is 
to offer the greedy and disoriented Montenegrins the chance to 
spread to <LOCATION>Herzegovina</LOCATION>. In this way they would be silenced -- 
they would not dare oppose the process of making <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> a 
Serbian province. They would perhaps not become a national 
minority, but a weak majority in their own state. The second 
reason reveals that the constructors of a greater-Serbia in 
<LOCATION>Bosnia</LOCATION> have difficulties. If the Muslim-Croatian federation is 
accomplished, there are good chances that the territories along 
the <LOCATION>Drina River</LOCATION> in <LOCATION>Eastern Bosnia</LOCATION> will be annexed to it, 
regardless of the fact that they are ethnically clean now. If 
Serbs oppose the tripartite federation and if <LOCATION>Bosnia</LOCATION> enters two 
confederations, with <LOCATION>Croatia</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Serbia</LOCATION>, there is the 
possibility that Serbian territories in <LOCATION>Bosnia</LOCATION> be divided into 
two separate parts. In this case, <LOCATION>Herzegovina</LOCATION> would be 
connected with <LOCATION>Serbia</LOCATION> through <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> as a member state of 
the alliance of Serbian states. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>DPS</ORGANIZATION>, led by <PERSON>Bulatovic</PERSON> and <PERSON>Djukanovic</PERSON>, keeps on denying 
<LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> as a state. In the alliance of Serbian states, 
although its name might be <LOCATION>Yugoslavia</LOCATION>, there is no place for 
Montenegrin individuality, there are no conditions to cherish 
the national, cultural, religious, and other authentic 
Montenegrin traditions. The <ORGANIZATION>Serbian Institute for the 
Protection of Monuments</ORGANIZATION> was given the task of renovating the 
Romanesque church of <ORGANIZATION>Sveti Luka</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Kotor</LOCATION>. After the renovation 
the original dome without a square pedestal was turned into the 
<ORGANIZATION>Raska School</ORGANIZATION> type dome with a high square pedestal. This example 
illustrates how dull the (post)communist <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> is. It also 
shows the Serbian attitude toward Montenegrin cultural heritage 
and its future in any union of Serbian states. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>DPS</ORGANIZATION> members who gave standing ovations to the university 
assistant from <LOCATION>Podgorica</LOCATION>, should know that they are participants 
in the crime being committed against <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> on their behalf 
and with their own hands. 
  The fact that this is interpreted as the people's wish does 
not change the essence. 

</TEXT>

