<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Tirana</LOCATION>, <DATE>January 6</DATE> (ATA) -- The region of <LOCATION>Ulcinj</LOCATION>, 
with eighty per cent Albanians, is now an objective of the 
Serbian headquarters. According to a report in newspaper 
RILINDJA on <DATE>January 5</DATE>, the <LOCATION>Valdanos Bay</LOCATION>, known for its beauty 
and riches along the <LOCATION>Adriatic Sea</LOCATION>, will be transformed in a 
military base. 
  In a recent press conference, the commander of the Serbian 
and Montenegrin military-naval forces, <PERSON>Mr. Dojcilo Isakovic</PERSON>, 
cited by the pro-government Montenegrin newspaper POBJEDA spoke 
about creation of a naval base in the bay of Valdanos, near 
<LOCATION>Ulcinj</LOCATION>, which will cover an area of 340 hectares. 
  Reacting against the military plans of <LOCATION>Belgrade</LOCATION>, the 
secretary of the party of the <ORGANIZATION>Liberal League of Montenegro</ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON>Mr. 
Miodrag Burzan</PERSON>, stressed that during the time of the former 
<LOCATION>Yugoslavia</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> possessed 1/10 of the seashore. Now, 
seventy-eighty per cent of the naval forces is concentrated in 
this place. This movement of the naval forces in the seashore of 
<LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> threatens in transforming this republic in a military 
base, stressed <PERSON>Burzan</PERSON>, adding that such projects, which are 
being planned even for the regions around the lake of <LOCATION>Shkoder</LOCATION>, 
aim at transforming <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> in a concentrated military camp. 

</TEXT>

