<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Tirana</LOCATION>, <DATE>June 14</DATE> (ATA) -- A delegation of the 
Republic of <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> arrived in <LOCATION>Tirana</LOCATION> on its way to the <ORGANIZATION>UK</ORGANIZATION>. 
The delegation is led by Premier <PERSON>Milo Djukanovic</PERSON> and composed 
of Deputy Premier <PERSON>Krunoslav Vukcevic</PERSON> and Foreign Minister 
<PERSON>Miodrag Lekic</PERSON>. 
  On the request of the Montenegrin part, the delegation was 
received in <LOCATION>Durres</LOCATION> by Premier <PERSON>Aleksander Meksi</PERSON> and Foreign 
Minister <PERSON>Alfred Serreqi</PERSON>. <PERSON>Mr. Meksi</PERSON> pointed out the contacts and 
dialogue are important for the development of the relations 
between the two countries. This is a principle of the Albanian 
foreign policy also applied in the relations between <LOCATION>Albania</LOCATION> and 
<LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION>Albanian Government</ORGANIZATION>, said <PERSON>Mr. Meksi</PERSON>, holds that 
both sides should find possibilities for a cooperation in the 
future in fields of mutual interest. He also mentioned aspects 
of the regional situation, reiterating <LOCATION>Albania</LOCATION>'s opinion on the 
events in <LOCATION>Bosnia-Herzegovina</LOCATION>, on the issue of the Albanians in 
<LOCATION>Kosova</LOCATION> and the relations of <LOCATION>Albania</LOCATION> with neighbouring countries. 
  <PERSON>Mr. Djukanovic</PERSON>, Montenegrin premier, pointed out the 
readiness for cooperation between <LOCATION>Montenegro</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Albania</LOCATION>, as 
neighbouring countries with common interests. He also spoke 
about the Balkan situation, laying the stress in the development 
of the dialogue between the two parties. 

</TEXT>

