  [Text] <LOCATION>Podgorica</LOCATION>, 18 <DATE>May</DATE> (TANJUG) -- Talks were held <DATE>today</DATE> 
between <PERSON>Momir Bulatovic</PERSON>, Montenegrin president and member of the 
<ORGANIZATION>Supreme Defense Council</ORGANIZATION>, and top <ORGANIZATION>Yugoslav Army</ORGANIZATION> officers. At the 
talks, they concluded that officers and commands of the <ORGANIZATION>Yugoslav 
Army</ORGANIZATION> have displayed a high degree of responsibility for the 
overall combat readiness of their troops under very complex 
circumstances. 
  As it has been announced, the commanders of the First, 
Second, and Third Armies -- <PERSON>Generals Jevrem Cokic</PERSON>, <PERSON>Bozidar 
Babic</PERSON>, and <PERSON>Dusan Samardzic</PERSON> respectively -- General <PERSON>Ljubisa 
Velickovic</PERSON>, commander of the <ORGANIZATION>Air Force</ORGANIZATION> and anti-aircraft 
defense, and <ORGANIZATION>Navy</ORGANIZATION> Commander Admiral <PERSON>Dojcilo Isakovic</PERSON> informed 
Bulatovic about the level of combat readiness of the strategic 
formations under their command, the implementation of measures 
set by the <ORGANIZATION>Supreme Defense Council</ORGANIZATION> relating to the security of 
the state territory under present conditions, further 
transformation of the <ORGANIZATION>Yugoslav Army</ORGANIZATION>, and other issues. 
  Stable financing, in line with the capabilities of the 
state, 
will enable the speedier resolution of problems in supplying 
units with state-of-the-art equipment and in securing better 
living standards for the <ORGANIZATION>Yugoslav Army</ORGANIZATION>. 

</TEXT>

